 " with characteristic, ",
 StyleBox["N",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " total)\n\t\nand we introduced the PoissonDistribution object in Example 6. \
When you want a value of the p.m.f. of a named distribution (including its \
parameter arguments) at a state ",
 StyleBox["x,",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " you issue the command\n\n\t\t\t\tPDF[distribution, ",
 StyleBox["x",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "]\n\t\n(The \"D\" in \"PDF\" stands for \"density,\" a word that will be \
motivated in Chapter 3.) For example, the earlier computation of the \
